facts.seriesTitle: Population below international poverty line (percent)
facts.fact_text: The proportion of the population living below the extreme poverty line declined from 2.8 % in 2001 to 1.1% in 2009.

facts.fact_text: The proportion of population living below the national poverty line increased from 16.2 % in 2001 to 22.5% in 2009.

facts.seriesTitle: Annual growth rate of real GDP per capita (percent)

facts.fact_text: In 2017, 98.0 % of the population was in range of at least a second-generation (2G) cellular signal

facts.seriesTitle: Annual mean levels of fine particulate matter in cities (micrograms per cubic meter)
facts.fact_text: In 2016, the annual population-weighted average mean concentration of fine suspended particles of less than 2.5 microns in diameter (PM2.5) was about 10.08 micrograms per cubic metre. This is above the maximum level for safety set by WHO of 10 micrograms per cubic metre.
